      "rationale": "Eleven constructs were assembled using production-representative 7.5 mm non-cannulated pedicle screws and 5.5 mm titanium rods, distributed across two independent laboratories (n=6 Lab A, n=5 Lab B). Components were drawn from the same production lot. Sample size supports statistical comparison per V&V 40 guidance for medium-consequence decisions. Achieved level meets required level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions should span the range of clinically relevant loading rates and environmental conditions; at minimum two conditions tested.",
      "rationale": "Testing was performed under a single quasi-static loading rate (5 mm/min) at ambient temperature per ASTM F1717. No elevated-temperature or cyclic pre-conditioning conditions were included. This limits the generalizability of the validation evidence to the single tested condition. Achieved level (2) is below required level (3); this gap is noted and accepted given the medium model risk and the conservative nature of quasi-static loading for yield and stiffness QoIs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation boundary conditions and loading protocol match experimental setup; fixture geometry and constraint conditions verified.",
      "rationale": "ASTM F1717 fixture geometry was replicated in the FEA model using CMM-measured fixture dimensions. Pin-joint boundary conditions were applied at the inferior fixture attachment point; displacement-controlled loading applied at the superior attachment, matching the test machine actuator displacement protocol. Loading rate effects are negligible at quasi-static conditions. Achieved level meets required level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
